  "_note": "Authored 2026-07-13 by standard/author-simcit.mjs FROM THE ENGINE — from the code that actually DRAWS: gameCanvas.js:416 does drawImage(this._spriteSheet, (frame-1)*48, (type-1)*48), and the sheet is images/sprites.png (via <img id=\"sprites\">, micropolis.js:41). An earlier version of this script authored from baseSprite.js:92 getFileName(), which composes obj<type>-<frame> and matches the 61 PNGs in sprites/. That function is DEAD CODE — exported and called by nothing. Grep proves a symbol exists, not that it is reachable. RULE 0: micropolis.js:42 polls sprites.complete and starts once true. A 404 ALSO sets complete = true (naturalWidth 0), so a missing sheet neither stalls nor throws — every drawImage silently draws nothing and the city runs with no trains, no planes, no monster.",
